A 45-year-old man has been arrested after allegedly murdering his 40-year-old girlfriend in Nazareth, Pinetown. It is alleged that on March 20 at 7.15pm, the woman was found by her friend at her home on Bhulose Road in Nazareth. According to police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, the friend had earlier received a call from the woman’s manager when she did not report for duty. “The victim was found dead with a bullet wound to the forehead. A case of murder was opened at the Pinetown Police Station for further investigation. “The police investigation revealed that the deceased was last seen with her boyfriend at her residence at 1.30am. The suspect received information that the police were looking for him and decided to hand himself over,” said Mbele. The man has been arrested and charged with murder. He will appear in court on Wednesday.